    "extract": "Phillips Edison & Company is an American REIT that owns and develops shopping centers throughout the United States. Founded in 1991, the company is headquartered in Sycamore Township, Ohio, and has offices in Salt Lake City, Utah,  New York City, New York and Atlanta, Georgia. The company wholly owns 268 shopping centers and has partial ownership interest in 21 other facilities in a combined 31 states. Its largest tenants by square footage leases included: Publix, Kroger, Albertsons, and Walmart."
